dct_description_sm: Map of Russia in Europe, pages 75 and 76 of the XXth Century Citizen's atlas--judging from state of various railways and difference with the 1912 edition's inset maps, this was likely taken from an edition later than 1908, but earlier than 1912.
Relief shown by hachures and spot heights.
Bar scales in "British Statute Miles," "Russian Versts."
Shows railways, district and country boundaries (by coloring), cities and towns, waterways.
